  "content": "takeaway: these numbers are directionally useful, but your mileage will vary. Always benchmark on your own hardware.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">06 / 08</div>\n</div>\n<!-- SLIDE 7: WHAT IT TOOK — engineering behind each backend -->\n<div class=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">What It Took</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 24px;\">\n    Behind<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-red\">corvia use &lt;backend&gt;</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 19px; margin-bottom: 28px;\">\n    One command to switch backends. Getting there was a different story.\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Three backend effort cards -->\n  <div style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px;\">\n    <!-- CPU -->\n    <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 20px; align-items: flex-start;\">\n      <div style=\"min-width: 100px; text-align: center; flex-shrink: 0;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size: 36px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--accent-green);\">0</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 600;\">PACKAGES</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-green); border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0; padding: 20px 24px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-amber); margin-bottom: 4px;\">CPU</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6;\">ORT default. Just works.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>",
